      <bioghist id="aspace_e0acb7beaf833f24c8959a69df83b50f">
         <head>Bio/Historical Note</head>
         <p>Mary Margaret Hall was a 1963 graduate of Madison College and a 1959 graduate of
            Washington and Lee High School in northern Virginia. She majored in Physical Education
            and was a member of the Athletic Association. An avid swimmer, she was a member of the
            "Porpoise Club" and obtained certification in water safety from the American Red Cross
            in 1960.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_614f6a68c47d609941577e41ed2ae4b5">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>This collection offers a glimpse into one physical education major's campus life during
            the late 1950s/early 1960s. Included are a letter of acceptance and room deposit
            receipt, 1958-1959; class schedules, appointments, testing schedules for freshmen, and
            laboratory directions for human physiology class; forms for a day trip and date,
            invitations to campus events and a 1963 commencement announcement.</p>
      </scopecontent>
